The leader of the APC in Cross River State, Mr Goddy Jeddy-Agba, who is the minister of state for Power, and a Board of Trustees (BoT) member of the party, Mr Clement Ebri, a former Senate Leader, Victor Ndoma-Egba, former minister of Niger Delta Affairs, Usani Usani and Senator John Owan-Enoh have resolved the over three years crisis which plundered the party. Mr Godwin Etim John, who led one of the two factions and has been picked as the interim state chairman of the party, informed Daily Trust of the development during an interview. “As it is now, the other group which was led by Sir John Ochala has agreed for the new found peace and unity for the consolidation of our formidable position in the state. We are all coming together to work for the party in the state, APC is unstoppable. 2023 is as sure as won already,” he said. Meanwhile, Ntufam Edim Inok who is leading a faction of the PDP in the state has said “there is no question about the popularity of his party”, insinuating that Cross River is a PDP state. Edem Duke rejects Cross River APC primaries results How reconciliation works in favour of Amosun, Okorocha, others New faction emerges in Cross River APC